      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MIKI B NZ (4) was Group 3 placed at Melton last month and was good in his two starts here over the carnival, beaten 6m into fourth in the Hondo Grattan Stakes before racing parked but boxing on for a midfield finish in the Chariots of Fire. Draws closer to the pegs than in any of those runs and his form reads well for this. GIPSY PRINCESS (2) came from the extreme outside so did well to clock in fourth last start. Also had wide barriers when recording three successive placings here earlier in the campaign so will enjoy this much more favourable draw. HUGO MAGUIRE NZ (7) could be close to a win after back-to-back placings here, the latest when he came from this barrier and chased Hollywood Strip for third. TUKAHA (8) wasn't far behind Hugo Maguire last start and won over this distance the previous time he raced here. LIGHT ME UP NZ (11) draws deep but is good enough to feature in a race like this if things go his way.",
